Text.Value: I can't wait to get outta this dump and never come back. Grab what you can before we scarper, yeah?

EditorData.NodeContext: Sigh at the beginning fo the sentence. Excited ot get out. Sick of the place.

Text.Value: Nuh-uh!

EditorData.NodeContext: Like two kids fighting back and forth 'Nuh uh!' 'Yeah huh!'

Text.Value: I'd like to buy it from you.
She always says the stuff I like is junk. I'm gonna make a killing on this! You'll see.
Yes she did.
Really? But she said... all right. Here. I guess.
Hmm. I'm not supposed to mention it to anyone, but I do have something pretty special in stock. A key.
As Mol would say - suit yourself.
No she didn't.
I'll be back with the money.
Hand it over. Now.
But she put me in charge of the shop! I thought... never mind. Here. You can have it, then.
Mol said I could have it.
My stores are always open to you - just make sure you give Ketheric a few knocks from me, yeah?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Nightsong arrived to Haven/dead, people know that Ketheric can be killed
EditorData.NodeContext: Gleeful in the thought of beating up the 'bad guy'

Text.Value: Huh... No, no! Don't tell me I dropped it? I'm an idiot.
I'm back about that key.
Welcome back. Are you, ahem, looking for something in particular?
What're you looking for?
What can I get you?
In the market for something special?

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Ahem' is said with gravitas, you're enjoying being a 'businessman'

Text.Value: If it was worth any coin, do you think Mol would have given it to you?
Mol knows it'll be safer with me - and so do you.
Oh no! I'm so sorry, I - I think I dropped it. This is so unprofessional, Mol is gonna kill me!
Ugh. Fine.
Take good care of that key.
You drive a hard bargain, but it's a deal. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Leave.
Yours is the first happy face I've seen in a good while.
Let me see what you have.
No way! This is my shop - that means I'm in charge of all the stuff in the shop. And that's that.
Thanks for bringing the crew back. If I open a shop in Baldur's Gate you're gonna get a discount! Not, like, a big one, but still.
You had something to do with the light, right? I knew it - this is the end for Ketheric. Stock up while you can!

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Nightsong arrived to Haven/dead, people know that Ketheric can be killed

Text.Value: Cause it's mine. Got it?
Better hurry, I've got loads of interested parties.
You got any stock for an extra special customer like me?
Go ahead! It's mine. Got it?!
Mol mentioned some 'silver junk' she'd found?
That's way too little. Here. Keep the change. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_2_463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
I'm alive, ain't I? What's not to like.
What does it look like? What does it open? What treasures await behind its lock? That's for one lucky buyer to find out.
Sure...

EditorData.NodeContext: Rolling eyes, player has said they would be back with the money once already.

Text.Value: Mol said never abandon your post, so I'm gonna keep the shop going. What do you need?
Shop's still open - what do you need?
Seems like you need some extra supplies. What'll it be?

EditorData.NodeContext: Little worried but trying to be 'professional'

Text.Value: Yuh-huh.
Mol can be cranky, and mean, but she looks after us. So, stock up, all right? 'Cause you need all the help you can get to bring her home.
What about it?
I mean... maybe.
This is a, ahem, valuable piece, so it's gonna cost a lot. And that is non-negot... non... the price isn't changing! ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])

EditorData.NodeContext: trying to sound like a professional

Text.Value: Check it out - we've gone legitimate, and Mol put me in charge. Whaddya need?
You got the coin this time? ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])

EditorData.NodeContext: Cheeky - you don't expect the player to have the coin.

Text.Value: Hm. I guess it is kind of old. Here. Birds of a feather.
Give it or I'm telling Mol on you.
Yes! That's my first negotiation. Here. Pleasure doing business with you.

EditorData.NodeContext: delighted. Saying 'negotiation' like it's a super posh business word

Text.Value: With all the other fabulous things you've found in this inn, why hold on to a dusty old key?
You mentioned you had a key?
No chance. That's too much.
Are you serious? Thanks so much! I've gotta tell Mol.
Mol gave it to me, said I shouldn't let it go to just any old jack-a-day.
Don't worry - it isn't leaving my sight!
Until she tells me that herself, I'm gonna hang onto it. Thanks.
Pleasure doing business with you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very dodger oliver twist, hamming it up a bit

Text.Value: I want to go back. Back to the way things were... What can I get you?

EditorData.NodeContext: Your friends are dead. Upset and grieving. Trying to get it together. Trying to shake it off and be professional in second setence.

Text.Value: Look - give it to me now, or I steal it later. The former is less embarrassing.

Synopsis:
Dialog with Mattis in Haven. He's a young tiefling boy who dreams of opening up his own shop in baldur's gate. He's delighted to be given the responsibility of the 'shop' in the Last Light Inn and does his best to sound more 'grown-up' and 'formal'. But he fumbles it a bit.
This is his main dialogue in Haven and covers all major states, Isobel and Mol kidnapped, the Inn attacked, tieflings dead, etc.
